cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about using reinforcement learning to learn tree-structured neural networks for natural language processing tasks. The most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper focuses on language modeling and sentence representation. The second likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper uses reinforcement learning to optimize the tree structures. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper uses machine learning techniques to improve natural language processing. The fourth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper uses neural networks to learn the tree structures. The fifth likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as the paper uses similar techniques to those used in computer vision, such as convolutional neural networks.
